ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Lecture-format in a class with<10 students. Dry; didn't cover the material we were expected to write about for take-home exams; self-taught entirely. Homework feedback not very helpful and received too late to improve future assigments.
If you're not a major, I recommend shopping around. I don't want to write off this class because phonology is interesting, but I think Tamas Biro tried to cover too much material this semester.
